Label: GLUT1,2
Comment: Human pancreatic beta cells contain GLUT1 and GLUT2 transporters, with GLUT1 predominant. Rodent beta cells predominantly contain GLUT2, which may account for differences observed in the toxicity of streptozotocin.

Label: PLC beta1,2,3
Comment: Pancreatic beta cells contain PLC Beta 1, PLC Beta 2, and PLC Beta 3. It is unknown which PLC or combination of PLC's are activated in response to G(q).

Label: ArgN-GCG(98-127)
Comment: The amide group at the C-terminus is not necessary for biological activity.

Label: ArgN-GCG(98-127)
Comment: The amide group at the C-terminus is not necessary for biological activity.

Label: cell, open)
Comment: Human pancreatic beta cells contain Kv2.1, Kv3.2, Kv6.2, and Kv9.3 voltage gated potassium channels. The channels are closed in a resting beta and channels open in response to depolarization. Open channels counteract the effect of closed ATP-gated potassium channels and thereby end stimulation of insulin secretion .

Label: FFAR1:FFAR1 ligands
Comment: The Free fatty acid receptor 1 (FFAR1 or GPR40) is located on pancreatic beta cells and binds to medium and long chain fatty acids (fatty acids having more than 12 carbon groups). FFAR1 is a G-protein coupled receptor that is coupled to Gq.
